    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a genus containing large, bushy-tailed, stocky ground squirrels native to mountainous areas such as the Alps, Carpathians, Tatra, and Pyrenees in Europe, the Rockies and the Sierra Nevada in the United States, and Northern Canada.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
